I think some said pretty insightful things, but in general, their style of parenting in my opinion is almost a luxury.

snippet.textDisplay: Honestly, man. Spanking works differently on everyone. I don’t mind spankings, or more specifically ass beatings of my children, because there will be situations where it requires an ass beating so they won’t do the same thing over and over again. But with that being said, it works two different ways. Either A: I spank my child, and they learn that what there doing isn’t right. Or B: I spank them and they resent me. I’ve learn growing up that when the child begins to resent a parent due to spankings, is often times because the parent spanks them to excessively. Spanking is fine. But please, make sure that after you spank your child, you sit down and genuinely talk to them and explain to them why you did what you did. And make them aware of what they did wrong. My parents did that to me growing, and I’m not fucked up...Well. Never mind, lol. Much love to everybody in the comment section. What do you guys think about spanking?

snippet.textDisplay: as a person in a family of 10 i can tell you for a fact that i have seen both a strict and lenient side to my parents parenting. sad to say, the lenient side doesn’t work well. my four younger brothers dont show respect, don’t have manners, and don’t know how to stand up for themselves whereas my older siblings, who were brought up in a more uptight household respect and care and understand things and even understood things at a very young age. you can’t let your kids have all the freedom. yeah it’s nice to have parents who are laid back and chill, but you have to find the barrier between chill and parent. set the boundaries first, then build the fun relationship. just my thoughts and opinions on what i’ve seen works and doesn’t.

snippet.textDisplay: I grew up with strict parents. I always had to ask before I could leave home. I had my dad tell me that if I left to see my friends, I wouldn't be allowed back inside. And that was when I was sitting outside in our front lawn crying because I would miss my friends birthday party. I had my phone searched at least twice a year until I was 17. And by then my grandparents still tried to pressure my parents to search my phone. I'm 19 now and in all honesty, I can barely make any decisions for myself. I'm vulnerable and I fall for things easily because I wasn't allowed to make mistakes. I get anxiety when someone takes my phone because I've grown up having my phone searched. I closed myself away from my family. And I'm still treated like a child.

snippet.textDisplay: In Sweden it's illegal to hit your child since 1966, that includes spanking as a "punishment". This is because studies have shown that kids that have been raised with violence are more prone to aggression, psychological problems and drugs/alcohol addiction. Sure every kid raised like this might not have all off these symptoms in their adult life, but that doesn't mean that the kids/adults won't have trauma from this act.

Also I think that lady that said she wasn’t parenting her kids after they move out, was really trying to say that she won’t be a big in her adult kid’s ear when it comes to HOW they are going to live their life.

Then her saying she’d be their friend, I think she meant she’d always be there to listen and give advice. But not necessarily tell you how without you asking for it.

My mom did a similar thing “18 and out of my house” and I come to her to be ‘parented’ like 5 times a week😅 however, she never tells me the IDEAL course of action with situations I deal with, mainly because I always have a tentative plan as well, so she may not think I need it. But I have just learned to ask “what would you do?” after I give my ideas. That’s helped tremendously.

I believe we learn not to touch fire because of the pain we felt when we did touch it and it hurt us. You do learn as a kid that something hot means ouch and you stay away from it. I think it depends on what the kid did, how old they are and what kind of punishment they deserve. I don’t rule out spanking though. Like I’ve said I’ve noticed two types of spanking and only one means well, the other one is an adult taking out their anger on a child. Don’t cofuse the two.

snippet.textDisplay: I mean as I was growing up my mom was my parent but she was also my best friend. And I had rules but I always had a lot of freedom to make me own decisions. I mean obviously when I was really young I wasn’t able to do everything I wanted with out talking to her but once I was 14/15 she started giving me more freedom and obviously there was things she didn’t want me doing so we would sit down and talk about it and she would tell me the consequences and I think it’s so important to sit down and talk to ur child about the consequences of their actions instead of yelling and telling them they aren’t allowed to do something because that’s just gonna want to make them do it more. My mom has never completely gone threw my phone but we have such an honestly relationship that I tell her EVERYTHING. If she needs my phone to look up something or do something I give it to her without worrying about her seeing something that she doesn’t know about.
